doc.after: North American hunting pre dates the United States by thousands of years and was an important part of many pre Columbian Native American cultures Native Americans retain some hunting rights and are exempt from some laws as part of Indian treaties and otherwise under federal law examples include eagle feather laws and exemptions in the Marine Mammal Protection Act This is considered particularly important in Alaskan native communities
